  "texts": [
    "LLMs rely on users's context to judge whether the user will interact with the recommendation.",
    "However, the users may have too many historical behaviors, or not all the historical behaviors are correlated to the query item.",
    "To this end, we utilize the item embedding from the filtering process to filter the related items,𝑪 (𝑓) 𝑢 = Top 𝐿 {𝒇 ⊤ 𝑖 • 𝒇 𝑗 | ∀𝑗 ∈ 𝑪 𝑢 },(8)where 𝑪 𝑢 denotes the user's historically interacted items.Prompt Design.",
    "The LLM prompt contains three parts: 1. fixed prompts, 2. user context, and 3. item content.",
    "The fixed prompts are used to set up the goal of the LLM Simulator."
